msContents.summary: Copy of a book about calendar systems, astrology, and fortune telling; references the Prophet Daniel as the source of much of the information.

msItem.title: Book in Arabic on calendars, planets and astrology.

name.#text: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

msItem.title: [Book in Arabic on calendars, planets and astrology].

supportDesc.extent: 154, ii leaves : 160 x 107 (124 x 75) mm, bound to 165 x 114 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paginated in Hindu-Arabic numerals, upper center, with some numbers skipped: [0]-8, 1-43, 45-182, 189-[300].

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in brown ink; pointed.

decoNote: Several diagrams, tables; rubrications in red.

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard with blind-tooled central diamond pattern and horizontal bands on the spine; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: The item is dated 1816 of the Christian era [Masīḥī] (p. 299)

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Joseph H. Haines (bookplate inside back cover).
